{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Those developing and providing generative AI systems (e.g.",
    "LLMs) will have to train, design, and develop the system in such a way that the content it generates does not breach EU laws, fully document and provide a detailed summary of the use of any copyrighted training data, and comply with strict transparency obligations.",
    "Examples of obligations include clearly notifying the user that they are interacting with an AI system or explicitly stating that the content was generated using AI.",
    "These obligations aim to protect against the infringement of intellectual property rights and copyright infringement and to ensure AI generated or manipulated content is clearly stipulated.",
    "Further reading is available from Hacker et al. (2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Further reading is available from Hacker et al. (2023)."
  ]
}